      "message": "[Critical] Line 2198: lastConnectivityRefresh_ is read and written from onICERequest() and connectivityChanged(), which can be invoked from different network/DHT threads. Because std::chrono::steady_clock::time_point is not synchronized here, this introduces a data race and the check/update is also not atomic, allowing multiple concurrent ICE requests to refresh simultaneously. Protect the timestamp and refresh decision with a mutex or use an atomic timestamp representation.\n```suggestion\n    bool shouldRefresh \u003d false;\n    auto now \u003d std::chrono::steady_clock::now();\n    {\n        std::lock_guard lk(lastConnectivityRefreshMtx_);\n        if (now - lastConnectivityRefresh_ \u003e ICE_REFRESH_THRESHOLD) {\n            lastConnectivityRefresh_ \u003d now;\n            shouldRefresh \u003d true;\n        }\n    }\n    if (shouldRefresh) {\n        JAMI_WARNING(\"[{}] ICE request from {}: refreshing stale network state\", getAccountID(), deviceId);\n        {\n            std::shared_lock lkCM(connManagerMtx_);\n            if (connectionManager_)\n                connectionManager_-\u003esetPublishedAddress({});\n        }\n        if (this-\u003econfig().turnEnabled \u0026\u0026 turnCache_)\n            turnCache_-\u003erefresh();\n    }\n```",
